quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,31,"He said, “So what is your business, O emissaries?”"
  51,32,"They said, “We have been sent to a criminal people,"
  51,33,"to unleash upon them rocks of clay,"
  51,34,"marked by your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord for the extremists.”"
  51,35,"Then We brought out all the believers who were in it."
  51,36,"Yet We found in it only one household of Muslims,"
  51,37,"and We left in it a sign for those who fear the painful punishment."
  51,38,"And in Moses<i class=""s"">(there is also a sign) </i>—when We sent him to Pharaoh with an evident manifestation."
  51,39,"But he turned away with his warlords and said, “A sorcerer or a madman.”"
  51,40,"So We seized him and his troops and flung them into the waters, and he was to blame."
  51,41,"And<i class=""s"">(likewise) </i>in<i class=""s"">(the people of) </i>ʻĀd{1}—We sent against them the Barren Wind,",footnotes:1:The pagan tribe of Prophet Hûd.
  51,42,"sparing nothing it came upon without rendering it like decayed ruins."
  51,43,"And<i class=""s"">(likewise) </i>in<i class=""s"">(the people of) </i>Thamûd{1}—they were told, “Enjoy yourselves for a while.”",footnotes:1:The pagan tribe of Prophet Salih.
  51,44,"But they defied the command of their Lord, so the <span class=""h"">Lightning</span>struck<sup foot_note=""81216"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup>them as they looked on,"
  51,45,"and they could not rise up, nor could they help themselves."
  51,46,"And<i class=""s"">(recall) </i><span class=""h"">before that, the people<sup foot_note=""81217"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>of Noah—indeed, they were a defiantly disobedient people."
  51,47,"And the universe—We constructed it with power, and We are surely expanding it."
  51,48,"And the earth—We spread it out. So how excellent are We who prepared it!"
  51,49,"And We created all things in pairs, that you may <span class=""h"">remind<sup foot_note=""81218"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">yourselves</span>."
  51,50,"“So flee to Allah; I am to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>from Him an evident warner."
  51,51,"And do not set up any other god with Allah; I am to you from Him an evident warner.”"
